review_blob: Pure white head, dark golden hue.  Not quite as hoppy as I expected and has a smooth finish.  Easy to drink and pleasantly hoppy.
beer_name: Long Trail Brewmaster Series Double IPA

review_blob: Tasty, like a saison with a tangy aftertaste.  Not quite as smooth as Saison Dupont, but a pretty smooth solid Farmhouse ale nonetheless...
Smooth fruity raisin flavor appealing to both taste and smell.  A beautiful mahogony color opening with a frothy head and finishing with an alaskan noserub of hops.  Great with peanuts.
strong Granny Smith aroma, VERY apple flavor with a biting aftertaste.  Its too appley and seems like a tart apple treat more than an easy drinking alcoholic beverage, and I LIKE cold beverages...
Smooth, very nutty and full of a caramel rich flavor.  Pleasantly surprised, but I think the caramel flavor is a little overbearing but still very drinkable...

Great Great IPA, Im not a huge IPA fan, but this one def rises above many others that Ive had.  Its got a fresh hoppy aroma and great deep golden appearance.  The burst of hop flavor is smoothed by a citrus aftertaste.  Very drinkable!!
Tastes like soy sauce!!  I dont know what else to tell ya...

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Definite hops, but a more smooth hops taste as opposed to many other hop infused ales.  The rich golden brown color screams hops and delivers with a fruity aftertaste.  The aroma is a rich fruity combination that comes through well in the beer.  Tasty slow drinking beer...
Smooth and subtle in taste.  Slight citrus flavor lingers for a short time.  Great beer for a bbq in the summertime.

Good Swillin beer.  If Im planning on having between 12-14 bottles then this is what Ill pick up (after Miller Lite).  To sit, sip and appreciate the flavor its not the ideal choice.  Great for horseshoes, fishing and general shenanigans.  It is perfect for the aforementioned because if ones spilled you dont drop to your knees and try to save every drop.  Drink on my friends, drink on...
Good knock off belgium, smooth with some citrusy hint and a nice aftertaste.
Unbelievably smooth for 9.8%.  Definite hint of bananas upon a deep whiff and an undertone of cherries throughout the sip.  Finishes a little malty and definitely draws you into another swig.
Smells a little like a basement in a frat house and tastes a little like what comes out of the keg after midnight.  Not so good, not complex, lacks any sort of interesting flavor.
citrus, orange peel aftertaste.  Clean and fresh finish.  Very orangy and smooth.
Malty caramel flavor with smooth aftertaste.  For 9% it goes down with ease.  Great beer start to finish.

Great citrus smell, a lot of sediment and Im not sure if every bottle is as sedimentary as this one is.  

Very complex with hints of citrus and sweet fruit sweet for a tripel but smoothe and very drinkable.
Nutty aroma with a dark, rich color and not much head.  Ver nutty and full flavor from start to finish.  Rich, smooth aftertaste containing hints of cocoa and coffee.
Plain, mild ale aroma with a very clear golden hue and not much head out of the bottle.  Subtle flavor with hardly any aftertaste and very little more than a weak ale taste.
Out of a can, not too bad.  If it werent so expensive it would be a terrific horseshoe beer, it just costs too much to drink a case and forget all about it the next day...
Pours a light golden amber. Smells of nuts and sports a light foamy head.  The sweet malt flavor finishes vy smooth without an overly alcoholic taste.

Pours mahogany with frothy head.  Strong nutty scent.  Surprisingly smooth flavor, great rich taste tat doesnt have an overly hoppy aftertaste.  Dark but not overpowering, an all around excellent, slow drinking beer.
Cool. Malty. Red. Nuts. Good with rich food or something spicy.  Definitely a full flavored beer to be drinken (or drunk, depending) slowly.

Vanilla/citrus scent with a slight hint of hazelnut.  Light color with little head and smooth, crisp palate.  Easy drinking beer with not much flavor and hint of spice in the aftertaste.  A great way for me to explain the taste would be "tame"...
Rich smooth flavor with a long dry aftertaste.  Theres a rich, chocolatey flavor that precedes a slight hoppy finish.
Smooth, malty aroma with a golden hue.  Sort of a flowery undescribable fruity flavor and great long aftertaste.  For a tripel it is undeniably smooth and has a great flavor from start to finish
GREAT.  The malty flavor is accented by a sweet, smooth aftertaste.  Its so creamy and malty for a dubbel, I was very very pleasantly surprised.  A new favorite for sure
Surprisingly tasty for a hoppy ale, clean taste with smooth aftertaste and hoppy overture.  Hints of plum in the aroma are overpowered by the hops.
UPDATED: OCT 10, 2007
Dark gold color with little aroma.  A little bitter for my taste, but a long solid flavor carries into a pleasant aftertaste.
Very little aroma, and very little head.  Clear golden color and nice lacing.  Fruity flavor, seemingly citrus, flows into a smooth light malty aftertaste.

Thick, frothy head lead by a smooth citrus aroma.  A muddy gold color masks an orangy body of flavor.  The aftertaste is dry and clean and not overly strong or fruity.  Solid lacing and overall a terrific beer.

Bottle, bought in Northern New Jersey. Solid, tall head with a rich dark color.  Aroma has a hint of raisins and fruit.  The flavor has a long pull of fruits, possibly currant with a smooth finish and chocolate finish.  Great drink from start to finish, for 11.3% its absurdly smooth, fantastic beer to drink slow and enjoy.

12oz. bottle: Very sweet with a touch of citrus stuck in the middle.  Clear headless appearance with little aroma and a weak (at best) aftertaste.  Stealing a classic line from a friend of mine, "I wouldnt kick her out of bed" but theres SO many better beers out there.
beer_name: Blue Moon Honey Moon Summer Ale

review_blob: Light crisp aroma, not as strong as I would expect.  Rich, fully bodied mahogony color.  Sweet caramel taste with a smooth aftertaste and pleasant bite.  It has a slightly hazelnut tint that rolls into the caramel and out very smoothly.
UPDATED: SEP 2, 2007
